#ğŸ“Œ Overview

The State Assembly Winter Session Simulation was an experiential learning intervention designed for BCA and MCA students to simulate the functioning of a State Legislative Assembly.

The activity replicated parliamentary structure including Question Hour, Bill Presentation, Debate, and Voting procedures to create a realistic policy discussion environment.

This initiative focused on competency development through structured debate, time-bound communication, and role accountability.

#ğŸ¯ Objectives

Develop structured communication skills

Enhance policy analysis and critical thinking

Improve time-bound decision making

Encourage leadership and collaboration

Build confidence in formal discussion environments

