Clear rules, time limits, and evaluation parameters were defined.

Phase 2 â€“ Policy Preparation

Teams researched assigned topics and prepared:

Opening arguments

Supporting data points

Counter arguments

Policy recommendations

Preparation time was intentionally restricted to simulate real-session pressure.

Phase 3 â€“ Live Assembly Simulation

The structured session included:

Question Hour

Bill Introduction

Debate & Rebuttal

Points of Order

Final Voting

Strict time monitoring was implemented to evaluate discipline and efficiency.

Phase 4 â€“ Debrief & Reflection

A structured feedback session was conducted to analyze:

Argument clarity

Time utilization efficiency

Leadership presence

Emotional control

Evidence-based persuasion

